  <brief_title>Carbon Dioxide Insufflation (CO2) and Warm Water Infusion (WWI) Versus Standard Air Insufflation (AI) for Unsedated Colonoscopy</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Valduce Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Valduce Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Due to the increasing demand for colonoscopy in clinical practice, great interest has
      recently renewed for unsedated colonoscopy. Both Carbon dioxide Insufflation (CO2) and Warm
      Water Infusion (WWI) have been advocated to improve patient tolerance for colonoscopy as
      compared to standard Air Insufflation (AI). This study is aimed at evaluating the performance
      of the above techniques versus AI in unsedated patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
